info.description:
# Get Started Here

This guide contains documentation for FBI's Most Wanted List API.

## Pre-requisites

There are no pre-requisites to using this API. Authorization tokens are not required. 

## Constraints
FBI's Most Wanted List API only supports the `GET` request.

## Data provided in the API

The FBI's Most Wanted List API presents the following suspect data in a JSON format:

- Name
    
- Race
    
- Address
    
- Nationality
    
- Date of birth
    

## Who is this documentation for?

This documentation is for:

- Developers who want to use data from the FBI's Most Wanted List API.
    
- Students who want to test and experiment with a publicly-available API
    

## Who isn't this documentation for?

This documentation is not for you if:

- You want to test API methods beyond `GET`.
    
- You want extensive information not provided in this API.
    

## API Access

You can access the API here: [FBI Most Wanted API](https://api.fbi.gov/wanted/v1/list)

## Variables
Only one variable is defined in this documentation.
| Variable | Value | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| base_url | https://api.fbi.gov/wanted/v1/list | API address |

## Success and Error Messages
The FBI's Most Wanted List API outputs standard HTTP messages to define successful and error events.
The following table shows possible error messages to expect while using the API

| S/N | HTTP Message | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 200 | Success | |
| 2 | 404 | Error | Entry not found |
| 3 | 405 | Method not allowed | Occurs when using other methods besides `GET` |

\r\n

\r\n

Subsequent attempts to contact Salinas' phone went directly to voice mail. Salinas was reported missing on June 16, 2013 (Father's Day), after she was unable to be located by family and friends.

\r\n

On August 6, 2013, two weeks after a substantial storm and flooding of the area, Salinas' remains were located in a desert wash basin behind a residence in Apache Junction, Arizona.

One trooper was wounded and the other was shot and killed execution-style at point-blank range. Chesimard fled the scene, but was subsequently apprehended. One of her accomplices was killed in the shoot-out and the other was also apprehended and remains in jail.
